  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Broadcast tapes of the weekly radio program, "Gayly Speaking." Debuting in 1973 on WDET-Detroit, "Gayly Speaking" was Detroit's first radio program "by, for, and about" gays and the gay liberation movement. The program ran for nearly ten years, when WDET replaced it with "Another Voice," a new program syndicated by Michigan Organization for Human Rights.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Programs present a range of topics and issues, such as sexism, "coming out," living alone, health, and health services. Some programs feature book and record reviews, gays involved in the arts, and gay organizations such as Detroit's Gay Switchboard.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Also recordings of a gay history course taught at the organization's offices in 1979.</subfield>
  </datafield>
